{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ac7yMd2HQ8uWFLkvpjakcj","type":"tool_result","content":"# Issue Summary\n\n**Title:** Implement component: task-ui #2\n\n**Core Request:** Build a React 18 TypeScript single-page application for task management, served via Nginx on port 3000.\n\n## Key Requirements\n\nThe component must deliver:\n\n- **Task Management UI** with list view, filtering (by category/completion status), add-task form, and edit modal\n- **API Integration** consuming task-api REST endpoints for CRUD operations and category fetching\n- **Visual Features** including completion checkboxes, category badges, due-date labels, and overdue highlighting (red text)\n- **State Management** via React hooks with automatic list refresh after mutations\n- **Error Handling** with dismissible banners for API failures\n- **Production Docker Setup** with multi-stage build (Node builder → Nginx static server)\n\n## Critical Implementation Notes\n\nThe specification emphasizes: \"VITE_API_URL is a build-time variable baked into the bundle by Vite; it must be set correctly at Docker build time\" and Nginx requires \"try_files directive falling back to index.html\" for SPA routing. Category filters must re-fetch after mutations, and add-task buttons must disable during requests.\n\n**Tech Stack:** React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Axios, Tailwind CSS"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f27ef23-9ff9-47c5-8737-d226c025c699","uuid":"54787e07-a794-4e91-9d6a-8e7d159cba11","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:55:22.153Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":287333,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Issue Summary\n\n**Title:** Implement component: task-ui #2\n\n**Core Request:** Build a React 18 TypeScript single-page application for task management, served via Nginx on port 3000.\n\n## Key Requirements\n\nThe component must deliver:\n\n- **Task Management UI** with list view, filtering (by category/completion status), add-task form, and edit modal\n- **API Integration** consuming task-api REST endpoints for CRUD operations and category fetching\n- **Visual Features** including completion checkboxes, category badges, due-date labels, and overdue highlighting (red text)\n- **State Management** via React hooks with automatic list refresh after mutations\n- **Error Handling** with dismissible banners for API failures\n- **Production Docker Setup** with multi-stage build (Node builder → Nginx static server)\n\n## Critical Implementation Notes\n\nThe specification emphasizes: \"VITE_API_URL is a build-time variable baked into the bundle by Vite; it must be set correctly at Docker build time\" and Nginx requires \"try_files directive falling back to index.html\" for SPA routing. Category filters must re-fetch after mutations, and add-task buttons must disable during requests.\n\n**Tech Stack:** React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Axios, Tailwind CSS","durationMs":6154,"url":"https://github.com/asdlc-repos/kaj-test-14182/issues/2"}}
